Bleve <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uphoenixxspiritwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phoenixx Spiritwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/01 10:46:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=131.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Again</span><hr size=1> Let's look on what I could have done. I could have told the ranger that he could not be in any of the lotto's because he was too low of a level but he could still bring his cousins lvl 53 shaman to help out. And he probably would have done that because he was a guildmate and a very nice person. Would it have been fair to him? No. He helped kill a lvl 60 mob by bringing ( at my request) his cousins 53rd shaman.<br>
<br>
     Second altnative. I could have let him lotto for shaman stuff and not even have told anyone he was playing someone else's account. Would this have been fair? No nor would it have been honest.<br>
<br>
     Sadly, you are missing my point. You feel that because this was a high level mob, the loot should have been lotto'd between those of equal level regardless of who put their effort into the slaying or not. I disagree. We can look at another example. Takes 30 people to do Nagy usually. Cloak of flames drops. A lvl 34 bard was present, rolled, and won. But wait, we deny him because everyone else on the raid was 45 +. Where is the fairness in that? Especially if he made a difference in the fight. That example I just gave you is actually a true story that happened not long ago but without the bard being excluded or denied the cloak. Haven't heard or seen any flames to that raid's leader decision. Wonder why?<br>
<br>
     Just because we dealing with a high level mob, doesn't make it right to exclude people who are lower then the &quot;norm&quot; for such an encounter if they are asked to come along. Normally you aren't going to see people who aren't of level to take on such a mob anyways.<br>
      That also brings a second point up. You had asked to join. We didn't actually HAVE to add you nor did you actually have to join. What did you get out of this? The same thing everyone who actively killed the turtle. A fair chance at a single item. If you had won, there would be no post. No flame. But because you had lost to a much lower lvl player you flame. It's that growing attitude that is self destructing alot of the higher level guilds. I believe CS broke up because Marr was fed up with the greed that was going on (second hand knowledge- I DO NOT know if this is entirely true but makes sense).<br>
<br>
     As far the item &quot;doing shit&quot; for the lvl 34 ranger let's look at the stats and effect. Though I can't confirm what lvl the effect actually starts working ( It's the same effect as the low lvl shaman attk speed buff, adds 20% spell haste). It's possible he may not be able to use the effect till later but it has nice AC, adds str, dex, hit points and some resists. These all are nice stats increases be it for a lvl 1 or lvl 60. If it didn't make leveling alittle bit easier by adding such stats, why even twink? The eyepatch is useful regardless of level.<br>
<br>
     If you don't like my lotto rules, then stick to your promise of not being apart of our raids. I will not let greed influence over fairness to everyone in any lotto. When it comes down to it, I made a single exception to what some of you feel are normal looting procedures. The exception was needed, and thus by making it I had to be fair to the person who was willing to do whatever it took to help out. The lotto could have gone either way but you lost and he won. Now you cling to a &quot;Higher lvl loot should go to high level people&quot; idea ignoring the fact that he had put his two cents in just like everyone else. That's not right in my book and you could  get 100 posts siding with you on this but it wouldn't change the fact you had a fair chance of winning the item like everyone else present only to lose to another person.<br>
      As far as him being able to complete the rest of the quest. It can be done. It may be a challenge but it's not out of his level range. He needs a lvl low 30's rare spawn griffon in Iceclad. Fear (Animal) and snare kite works fine. Saw a level 33 necro do this just fine ( using fear and pet). The dire wolf stalker is more common and near the same level as stormfeather. The last part is rather more time consuming then it is difficult. That's it.<br>
<br>
   Until a reasonable arugment can be presented, I am sticking to my guns. I am sorry if we see differently. We both now know better of the other person feelings regarding how lotto's should be done. All I ask was that you respect my decision even if you did not like it. And again, I would have gladly heard you out before you choose to log out without presenting your argument. You're not a bad person nor do I hate you. We simply don't agree on something that effects what raids we ask to be apart of.<br>
<br>
Phoenixx Spiritwind<br>
Still a pathfinder dammit<br>
